{
  "texts": [
    "This touches on the general question of how a dialogue management approach that is suited to such explanatory contexts might look.",
    "Most likely, such dialogue management systems will have to rely on different principles than current state-of-the-art systems that retrieve information to fill into a limited number of pre-defined slots.",
    "An important related question is to define the speech acts or dialogue moves that a dialogue system could use to effectively move the explanatory dialogue further towards achieving the overall objectives.",
    "An important point for future work will also be to develop approaches by which misalignments, misunderstandings, biases and incorrect assumptions made by a user can be identified and resolved.",
    "This would facilitate a more informed and accurate understanding of the system's explanations."
  ]
}